values:
some of my friends are incredibly lame.
aka lexi.

omgz i hate my life.
it sucks so much.
no one understands me.
i have to work sooo much
and i couldn't go to chiodos last night
and i was like so upset.
and school sucks.

livejournal, you're the only one who really gets me.

psychic!

updates:
1. nhs was the other night. i learned that i can't sit up straight and be still for two hours.
2. cross country is over. i'm sad...but happy. districts was friday and i pr'ed, and broke 25. it was a good way to end the season. 
3. school sucks. i'm doing better though, i guess.
4. work sucks. tonight, everyone was really drunk and they didn't tip us.
5. i made $30 in tips last weekend.
6. i have sat IIs next weekend.
7. we got a new girl at work, and katie quit.
8. i've been to applebees twice this week, in case you wanted to know.
9. i can drink pepsi/coke now.
10. this is the first time i've listened to taking back sunday for a while.
11. i hate lexi.


i guess you could say that life is good.

sooooo...classes after two weeks.

ap stat: so so boring. after taking calc...where's the challenge? i'm extremely glad it's only an hour long.
seminar: when i do work, i'd say it's pretty helpful.
senior seminar: boring. the majority of people in my class=not smart.
ap english: i'm actually kind of bored with this, too. discussing the same books for weeks is getting old.
c lunch: not cool after having a lunch for the past three years. i like how it breaks english up though.
ap chem: surprisingly, i enjoy it. i actually like doing the work...which is weird.

so basically, dropping out now would be awesome. not really. but yeah.

5!



ap calc. i was so happy. 3 on bio but whatever.  


anyway...
my summer course is almost over!
i've barely started my summer reading.
i've barely reviewed for the sats.
i've barely done any college stuff.
basically, i'm screwed.
fun summer, eh?

oh. i saw the killers on saturday.
and warped tour was last friday.
they were both pretty fun.
so...bye.
i am so out of it.

sometimes i wonder why i suck at life and stay up until three in the morning doing nothing.
it's almost as bad as lexi.

ridiculous.









anyway...
my friends are back.

i saw ace enders last night with cute is what we aim for, danger radio, and powerspace.
he was amazing.
i didn't actually see powerspace.

all my friends have left me.























and i am bored as anything.

i just got back from florida today.
the first person i saw was rashad, which was kind of random but cool.
and then dana and shawn. and then megan.
i got tanner. and i swam with dolphins. and the water in florida smells weird.
i need to go see ace next weekend.
but unless rashad got me a ticket tonight, at the moment, i don't have one.
i also don't have a ride home.
work tonight was kind of not fun.
the people were really messy, some guy told me he was going to cut off my hand, and no tip.
my leg hurts.
i didn't have to see lexi for eight days.
it was awesome. 
i'm kind of tired and this is kind of pointless.
so i'm gonna go make the world a better place.

i have work tonight at seven. it's gonna suck (like lexi). i'm gonna get out of there so late. 

ap tests are over. it's such a relief. i can actually do nothing this weekend. no studying at all. i still have to write a beat poem but whatever. i don't even want to think about my results for the tests. or for the sats, even though i should be getting them pretty soon. 

we went to glaxosmithkline yesterday for ap bio. my group had three whole people in it! awesome. we didn't get to see the animals, but it was still pretty interesting. plus, we got a day off from school, didn't have to go in dress code, and got a free lunch. after that, carrie, meghan, and i went to olph for field day to see our (meaning mine and meg's) moms dance. but we missed it by like five minutes. lame!

i watched the original producers two times yesterday. i love it so much. it's great. the first time i watched it with my mom, my grandmom, and hayley. then later meghan and carrie came over after we had an unsuccessful trip to visit amanda, and we started it again. they had to leave before it was over though. but bill and dana and then shawn came over as it was finishing. oh! lexi went to new york yesterday so i didn't have to deal with her on the trip! it was so great. i have found a new way to torture her, and it's very fun.

i'm going to see rookie of the year with capitol risk, the scenic, the wonder years, and maybe someone else on thursday with meghan, eryn, dana, and carrie. i don't really know why i'm going considering i don't really listen to any of them, but it should still be pretty fun.

i don't understand why our teachers decide to give us 25 projects/papers now, at the same time. it's so stupid. and they can't move the day of a test that half the class is missing because of the ap tests back a day, but they can make a day to read crappy beat poems that we wrote. why are they so dumb? like lexi.

my arm hurts and i think i'm gonna go make some tea. i need to wake up.

right now i should be writing my atomic bomb essay. but what am i doing instead? not that. i really do need to stop procrastinating.
so here's a little update:
-track is over
-calc is over
-i'm going to fail bio
-we're going to florida
-my summer is basically nonexistent
-i don't even know how i did on the ap calc exam
-going to bayside instead of prom was amazing
fun stuff, i know.

this weekend sucked. i had to take the sats and work while sick. luckily, i got to leave work after three hours. i don't know what i would've done if i hadn't been able to leave. died maybe...so sats again in june for me!

we won all three volleyball matches tonight, which is uncommon for us. our record is pretty not good. if we didn't have a flex day tomorrow, i think i'd kill lexi. 

ace enders is coming! which is kind of awesome. unfortunately, he's coming with cute is what we aim for, danger: radio, and powerspace. they're not bad, but i don't listen to them too much. andrew de torres is pretty cool though. 

may 13th = best day ever

shore this weekend. it's gonna be pretty lame. no one's gonna be there. 

i need a camera.

i am tired. and my arm hurts. i really need to go to bed.

shawn hates me
almost as much as i hate lexi.

maybe.

fuck it.
whatever.

man, i hope it doesn't happen.
it'd be so weird.

to all my fans, i know it may seem that i have abandoned my duties of writing about my hatred for lexi, but i have not. not at all. school has been okay lately. nothing special. today was surprisingly easy. review day in calc, destinos in spanish, nothing much in biology, and amex doesn't even count. all we did at track were stairs and sprints in the back hallway. also easy. i don't know why, but for the past few days i've been really pissed off and i don't know what. probably mostly lexi. but i'm assuming it's also a combination of an extreme lack of sleep, homework, and ridiculous track practices. on our first day of practice we did a 5.5 mile distance run. second day, 16 400s. third day, 5 mile distance run. fourth day, 6 800s. i was only there for four of them though. but still, even four is a good workout. but seriously, for the first week of practice...it's ridiculous. i blame it all on lexi. 
anyway. silverstein was a few weeks ago. it was pretty awesome. i went with dana, carrie, and bobbi and we saw eric, kyle, and two other kids that go to ridley that i don't know. but whatever. it was pretty intense for protest the hero and a day to remember. then for the devil wears prada it was completely insane. after their set was over, we went in the back to find carrie because she had gotten pushed back. then during silverstein, me and dana went in the back where all the pits were. it was actually really fun.

anyway. tonight was weird. we watched wkuk tonight. funny stuff. it's a shame so many people missed it. dude. freaking. unnecessary. okay? like why? i don't have too much homework this weekend. and i already finished my calc outline! but not bio. i didn't even bring that home. i've recently realized that i'm probably going to get a * on both of the ap exams. and yes, that is lower than a 1. i can't wait until may 13th. ap calc, ap bio, and track will all be over. and i will be happy. i love how i'm so eager for track to end and it's only a week into the season. whatever. i really need a break. work tomorrow at one. whoo! hopefully it won't be long. i'm kind of tired of writing. i'm out. lexi, i hate you.

NO ONE was listening to her. they were all too drunk. i got an 80 on my last calc test. it was pretty cool. um...i don't know what to do...

lexi, dana, ashley, bobbi, and i went to see chiodos on sunday. they played with the devil wears prada, scary kids scaring kids, and emery. and this random opener. i think they were called trophy stars. i wasn't a big fan of them but the drummer seemed pretty  good looking from semi far away. by the time we got there it was pretty full, so we just decided to stay back on the step part since we could see pretty well there. the devil wears prada was good. almost every one in that band was attractive, too. scary kids scaring kids was awesome. emery was alright but we didn't know them that well so when they came on we went in the back to buy merch and we got to meet pouyan! we got a picture with him...but dana blinked. and i gave him a hug. we almost met tyson twice but each time just as we were about to go up to him, he left. the second time was after the show at wawa. he walked up and i was like "hey" and he kind of smiled at me. then he went inside for like two seconds, came out, and was surrounded. chiodos was amazing. craig owens....well, he just seems like a very sexual person. lexi decided that we should crowd surf during "there's no penguins in alaska". she made it to the front but they dropped bobbi and ashley and i kind of got thrown into the middle of the hardcore dancing pit. but it was okay because it actually didn't hurt and this kid who was pretty cute helped me up. halfway through the opening band we turned around and rick and jason were standing there. jason's pretty cool but rick's kind of creepy. after sunday i thought he was okay though. until he started like semi stalking bobbi. but in general, it was a fun night.

so i did this instead. 

lexi = hate

underoath was on sunday. i have to say it's probably the best show i've ever been to. they were amazing. i went with dana, eryn, lexi, rashad, and jeremy. rashad and jeremy got to meet spencer and aaron because rashad was interviewing spencer. they were with maylene and the sons of disaster, poison the well, and every time i die. maylene was good, although i didn't really know them at all. poison the well sucked. every time i die was good too. underoath was amazing. our show was filmed for their concert movie thing so we'll all probably be on there which is pretty awesome. i was basically front and center for all of underoath and about second row for everyone else. i absolutely hated the kid who was behind me. he was ridiculously annoying. i really want to see them again. next year...i can't wait until their new cd comes out. dude. seriously. wow. 

i'm tired, as usual. cross country's over. it's sad but nice too. i think stan thinks i'm doing winter track. hah. no. districts was fun on friday. i dropped like thirty seconds off of my time. we played ultimate frisbee in the rain. i think that made me sick but whatever. i had work on saturday. it wasn't too bad. i have it again on sunday. whoo. i hate homework. so much. halloween's tomorrow.

essays are stupid. they don't help anyone. they aren't fun to write. they aren't fun to read. seriously, what's the point?

i'm tired. i should get some more friends who can drive.

dude i am tired. psats were today and they were a total party. and my last meet at rose tree for the year was today. i can't believe i only have one more year of running there. after all the races we went back into the woods and found our tree and all the seniors carved their initials into it. that'll be us next year. weird. we didn't win the sportsmanship award even though we totally should have. i mean lower merion won it. that was the meet that started two hours late and they made us all run together which sucked. lexi's movie party is now but i'm not going until later because emily's birthday party is also now even though only like four people are here at the moment. i need to do a lot of homework and write an essay and figure out what we're doing in calc. tomorrow should be fun. but not really. i wish i was down the shore right now with some cool people. unfortunately, i'm not.

i did pretty bad in my workout today. i really don't know why though. it shouldn't have been that hard and i wasn't really tired. i just couldn't do it. i was six seconds under on my last 400 after running three and three quarters miles and i didn't think that was hard and it didn't feel like i was going any faster than i had been before. i don't know what was wrong with me. nine more days. 

i have a calc test the day of districts. that sucks. a lot. i still don't know any bio. but we have a half day tomorrow so hopefully, somehow, i will learn it all then...which i doubt i will. we started reading the adventures of huckleberry finn today. even though we're not done everything with the scarlet letter. it's actually pretty good. me and dana read a chapter and a half out loud in accents and it was funny. which is a surprise. you know who isn't funny? lexi. yesterday i was trying to get her to do winter track, but she kept saying no. i'm not doing it. i just wanted her to do it so it could inflict high amounts of pain on her.

i'm am extremely tired and i'm not done my homework and i don't know anything for bio and i don't know what's going on in calc and lexi is annoying as ever. i hate school. luckily, i have less than two weeks of cross country left. there are a lot of people who've been pissing me off lately and i don't really know why. and most of them are really random people...besides lexi. ms mac said lexi and eryn and dana and meghan were immature. i told lexi she should have made a big speech about how she had the power of immaturity to rule the class and to stand on the desk and then when she was done talking to sing heavenly music. but because lexi is such an idiot, she didn't do any of that. she just said, "um. oh. okay." amex is really boring. i could not ever actually go to class and still pass it. there has to be someone to keep everyone amused by doing stupid things. i think mac hates the academy kids. because she doesn't get mad at anyone else, mainly scott or john, when they're talking or anything. mr. boehm likes us though.

this weekend was alright. friday i went to gap then lexi's house. saturday i went to lexi's and shawn made friends with the little kid next door while he was skateboarding. sunday we had a cyo meeting and we ate ice cream. there are some people there who are really annoying. then me and dana and meghan and lexi had a homework party at my house. then eryn and michelle and cindy and bill came over so we stopped. eventually, everyone left except for lexi. she refused to leave and she slept over. i didn't even ask her to stay. she just did. she's so annoying and i hate her so much. why would i want to have a sleepover with someone who i hate. and she made us listen to bullet for my valentine while we were falling asleep. it was horrible. she left at like 12:30 today so, luckily, i didn't have to spend all day with her. i was going to get my permit this weekend but the place was closed for colombus day. that was actually probably lexi's fault. so next weekend...hopefully.

 homework sucks. school sucks. i'm really glad we had off today. if we didn't there would be no way i would've gotten all of my homework done. 

only 2/3 weeks of cross country left! 

would you not give up and not lay down until i'm found?

i am extremely tired. school sucks. lexi sucks. they've been giving us a ridiculous amount of homework lately. it's the scarlet letter's fault.  do we really need to read like 25 chapters a night? no. i have no idea what's going on in calc at the moment. which isn't good. and i've only been getting like six hours of sleep if i'm lucky. i fell asleep like four times in calc today. that's probably why i don't know what we're doing. but even the people who stayed awake don't know what they're doing. so i don't know. i can't wait until cross country is over, only because i'll have like an extra two and a half hours to do homework and sleep. which should be pretty amazing. people are so weird. like...why?

so we went down the shore this weekend. it was really fun except for the fact that lexi was there. she pretty much ruined it for everybody. i came in tenth place at the meet today. that means i'll be in the paper. in the top ten spots in the race, seven of the girls were from ridley. we won. against both teams. we beat them by a lot. um...i'm tired. i didn't fail bio. and that's all. bye.

i am very tired. we're leaving for the shore at 9:30 tomorrow morning and i haven't packed yet. hah. oh well...i can pack in about two minutes. i hate homework. i hate school. i can't wait until summer. only like 42 weeks of school left. at least my bio and calc tests are over. i have a slight break this weekend.

anyway. not much is going on. lexi annoyed me today as usual, but what else is new? she made me watch like 50 final fantasy x videos that were all stupid. so i left. i miss seeing everyone in school. i never get to talk to a bunch of people i used to talk to all the time. sometimes that's a good thing, but sometimes it's not. i have 1.4 mb left on my ipod. i have to get rid of some stuff.
